  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Preserving the Future: Strengthening Iraqi Religious and Ethnic Minority Communities in Iraq</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Iraq&apos;s ethnic and religious minorities</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="4">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project will work towards: 1) Conflict-affected ethnic and religious minorities are less vulnerable to trafficking, labor exploitation and violence related to displacement; 2) Ethnic and religious minorities better contest government discrimination and violence in the court system; 3) Ethnic and religious minorities with severe impairment due to traumatic stress have improved access to mental health and medical care; 4) Ethnic and religious CSOs improve accountability of governorate and district level officials for ensuring equal access to government resources and services for minority communities; 5) Key stakeholders advance the passage of the Law on Minorities (Law) through the Iraqi Council of Representatives and the Iraqi Kurdistan Region Parliament; 6) Ethnic and religious civil society organizations are trained in conflict resolution; 7) Majority religious leaders support ethnic and religious minority rights; 8) Ethnic and religious minorities resolve land tenure conflicts through the legal system; 9) Iraqi youth learn tolerance and actively support religious and ethnic diversity; 10) Iraqi journalists more effectively report on ethnic and religious minority rights and protection.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">This project will empower Iraq&#x2019;s ethnic and religious minorities to more effectively assert their rights, and help ensure their long-term survival during a time of increased ethno-sectarian violence. The project will help minority communities, including displaced populations, to develop the skills to advocate effectively for government services; and will expand community councils to proactively identify sources of conflict and to mitigate them through mediation.</narrative>
  </description>
